<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="90" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,719,1827]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,828,853]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is unique in its significantly concaved inner side of the slender gonostylus and the long and strong apical tooth arising from a lobe on the dorsal margin. The species is also characterized by two long flagellate setae on the inner side of gonostylus; tegmen trapezoid, parameral apodeme continuously sclerotized forming a central strip on dorsal side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="90" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,719,1827]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,436,972,997]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Description (male).</emphasis>
Color. Head and thorax dark brown; antennae, palps, abdomen and hypopygium yellowish-brown; mesonotum brown; legs pale brown; wings fumose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,719,1827]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1044,1069]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[280,365,1044,1069]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,885,907]" captionTargetBox="[166,1407,206,859]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,193,871]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11. Mohrigia scrobiculata sp. nov., male, holotype [SM 00711]. A, palps, lateral view; B, 4 th flagellomere, lateral view; C, apex of foretibia, posteroventral view. Scale bar = 0.10 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837177/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Figs 11</figureCitation>
A, B). Eye bridge with 3 rows of facets. Maxillary palps 3-segmented, basal segment with 1 seta; 2nd segment with 5 setae; 3rd segment with 4–5 setae. Length/width index of 4th flagellomere: 2.22–2.57.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,719,1827]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,1116,1141]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Thorax.</emphasis>
Anterior pronotum with 3 setae, episternum 1 with 3 setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[967,1043,1116,1141]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1058,1139,1116,1141]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[186,1423,734,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,695,1902]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Wings, dorsal view. A, Mohrigia cylindrata sp. nov. (holotype); B, Mohrigia globulosa sp. nov. (holotype); C, Mohrigia angusta sp. nov. (holotype); D, Mohrigia notolobos sp. nov. (holotype); E, Mohrigia scrobiculata sp. nov. (holotype); F, Mohrigia orthacantha (Yang, Zhang &amp; Yang, 1993) (neotype). Scale bar = 0.50 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837183/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
E). Wing length 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.42" metricValueMax="1.44" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="19" pageNumber="90" unit="mm" value="1.42" valueMax="1.44" valueMin="1.4">1.40–1.44 mm</quantity>
, width/length: 0.38. c/w: 0.63–0.68. R1/R: 0.42–0.50. r-m, stM, M1 and M2 bare, CuA1 and CuA2 bare. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1380,1436,1151,1176]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,239,1190,1215]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="21.[151,250,885,907]" captionTargetBox="[166,1407,206,859]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,193,871]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 11. Mohrigia scrobiculata sp. nov., male, holotype [SM 00711]. A, palps, lateral view; B, 4 th flagellomere, lateral view; C, apex of foretibia, posteroventral view. Scale bar = 0.10 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837177/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
C). Length of spur/width of foretibia 0.82–1.03. Length of femur/length of metatarsus: foreleg 1.84. Length of metatarsus/length of tibia: foreleg 0.49–0.51, hind leg 0.42–0.45. Length of hind tibia/length of thorax 0.79– 0.97. Claws toothed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,719,1827]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,1298,1323]" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Hypopygium</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[369,455,1298,1323]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[203,1383,424,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[198,1387,416,1928]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 10. Mohrigia scrobiculata sp. nov., male, holotype. A, left gonostylus, ventral view [SM 00711]; B, gonocoxite, ventral view [SM 00711]; C, gonocoxite (paratype), ventral view [SM 00678]; D, gonostylus, dorsal view [SM 00711]. Scale bar = 0.10 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837175/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="90">Figs 10</figureCitation>
A–D). The gonocoxite as long as the gonostylus. The gonostylus slender and inner side significantly concaved, densely setose on the apicoventral part, with a long and strong apical tooth arising from a lobe on the dorsal margin of gonostylus, two flagellate setae on the inner side of gonostylus present. Hypopygium without an intercoxal lobe. Tegmen trapezoid, parameral apodeme continuously sclerotized forming a central strip on dorsal side. Aedeagus relatively short. Sternite 10 with 1 seta on each half.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
